WorldStage Newsonline– Abbey Mortgage Bank Plc, a  mortgage bank quoted on the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) has released a forecast of its performance for the fourth quarter (Q4) 2020 with expected gross earnings of N620.525 million. The company also projected a loss after tax of N654.405 million during the period. The company also projected a significant rise in cash and cash equivalents at the end of the period as N10, 074,237 from N6,558,562 at the beginning of the period.